    <stitle>BE 200 BUS FRONT END AND BODY COMPONENTS - ADJUSTMENTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ADJUSTMENTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Hood Adjustment And Alignment</title>
            <para>The BE Series front hood adjustment is done by moving the hinge plate attachment located at the front
                cross bar assembly.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust the hood forward or aft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust hood forward and back (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f47006307">Figure 307</hotlnk>), loosen the hinge mounting bolts at the mounting
                    plate on the front cross member.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the hood forward or aft as required.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the distance between the rear edge of hood and clearance to cowl.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the hinge plate mounting bolts and torque to 50 to 55 LBF-FT (68 to 75 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f47006307" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006307.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 307. Hood Hinge Adjustment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HINGE MOUNTING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CROSS MEMBER HINGE MOUNTING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD CROSS BAR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
